lease find enclosed my health and safety site evaluation report following my recent visit to your premises. The report identifies issues relating to health and safety standards that could impact on your business which we discussed during my visit.</span></p> <p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The premises&nbsp;consists of reception, offices over 2 floors, warehouse with mezzanine storage.</span></p> <p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The following are key areas, where I believe that actions are necessary to help ensure statutory compliance and to help maintain the health, safety and welfare of your employees whilst they are at work. The details are summarised below:</span></p> <p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Management of Health and Safety Documentation:</span></strong></span></p> <ul> <li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Inadequate contractor monitoring</span></li> <li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">No mains gas equipment checks or&nbsp;suitable records of portable electrical appliance testing</span></li> <li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">No Thorough Examination and servicing of lifting equipment (fork lift truck)</span></li> <li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Drivers of own vehicles do not supply documented vehicle checks</span></li> <li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Management monitoring of health and safety is need of improvement</span></li> <li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Fire risk assessment requires review with no fire plan included in the fire risk assessment, the assembly point is not clearly designated / apparent&nbsp;and there is insufficient recording of fire evacuation tests</span></li> </ul> <p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><br />Management of Practices and Procedures:</span></strong></span></p> <ul> <li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Inadequate or no arrangements in regard to the possibility of substance / alcohol abuse in relation to occupational driving&nbsp;</span></li> <li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Unsuitable access equipment in use or poor maintenance arrangements for access equipment</span></li> <li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Inadequate or no arrangements for loading and unloading activities on the mezzanine floor</span></li> </ul> <p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Management of the Premises:</span></strong></span></p> <ul> <li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Steps and stairways require improvement</span></li> <li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">No annual servicing of air conditioning units</span></li> <li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">No Safe Working Load plaques on all racking and inadequate arrangements for competent person examination of racking</span></li> </ul> <p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Health and Safety Risk Management:</span></strong></span></p> <ul> <li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">No documented health and safety consultation information</span></li> <li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Risk assessments for display screen equipment, hazardous substances and young persons require attention</span></li> <li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Emergency lighting check logging should be improved</span></li> <li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Lone working activities to be reviewed with regard to field sales staff</span></li> <li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Arrangements in place for risk of violence and aggression to be reviewed, potentially for the field sales staff</span></li> </ul> <p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">I will introduce you to&nbsp;your new &nbsp;electronic Safety Management System which includes the following online support tools, as agreed at the next visit which should take place early in the new year:</span></p> <ul> <li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Compliance Manager</span></li> <li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Risk Assessment Wizard</span></li> <li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Safety Management Documentation</span></li> <li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Accident Records</span></li> </ul> <p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The use of this electronic part of our service will enhance your ability to manage your health and safety needs and responsibilities and will enable you to effectively delegate tasks to your key employees. The system will electronically store all your key safety related documents and will automatically advise you when certain safety related tasks / actions should be undertaken.</span></p> <p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Detailed below is my proposed action plan which details the issues discussed during my visit, and in particular those which fall short of legal compliance and current recommended best practice and provides guidance for you to enable you to address the matters raised.</span></p> <p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The Enforcing Authorities could regard such matters as a &lsquo;material breach&rsquo; of legislation which could give rise to formal action being taken by them to ensure compliance.</span></p> <p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">I have also included a Health and Safety Compliance Review which comprises of a detailed overview of your current health and safety rating using a traffic light system.</span></p> <p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Should you require any further support or wish to discuss how we can further assist you in achieving health and safety compliance. Please do not hesitate to contact me or ring our 24 hour Advice Service on 0844 892 2772 option 2.</span></p> <p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Yours sincerely, </span><br /><br /><br /><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Paul Jackson<br />Business Safety Consultant</span></p> <p><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"> Email address: paul.jackson@peniinsula-uk.com</span><br /><br /><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Send by email to: linsay.wood@salonpromotions.co.uk</span><br /><br /></span></p>";
